# Sentential Logic: Supplementary Exercises

These are optional exercises, for students seeking more practice.

## Review

```{.QualitativeProblem .ShortAnswer submission=none}
1  Write down the definition of validity, without looking it up. Then check your answer.
```

## New Symbols

```{.QualitativeProblem .ShortAnswer submission=none}
2  Write down each of our five connective symbols, along with their name ('conjunction', 'disjunction', etc.) and what they mean. (Use the keyboard shorthands to type in each symbol.)
```

For each of the following, rewrite it using English in place of the
connectives:


```{.QualitativeProblem .ShortAnswer submission=none}
3 (P ∧ Q)
```

:::spoiler
The $\wedge$ symbol means 'and'. So: '(P and Q)'.
:::


```{.QualitativeProblem .ShortAnswer submission=none}
4 (P ∨ Q)
5 ¬P
6 ¬¬Q
7 (P ↔ Q)
8 (P → Q)
```

:::spoiler
|4 (P or Q)
|5 It is not the case that P
|6 It is not the case that it is not the case that Q
|7 P if and only if Q
|8 If P then Q
:::

## Parsing

For each of the following, determine whether or not it is a sentence in our
language, and, if it is, whether it is in informal notation or official
notation. If it is not a sentence, explain why not. If it is, parse it into a
syntactic tree (on paper).

9.  $\neg A$
10.  $(\neg P)$
11.  $\neg (P)$
12.  $\neg (Q \rightarrow P)$
13.  $\neg Q \rightarrow P$
14.  $\neg P \wedge Q$
15.  $\neg (P \wedge Q)$
16.  $\neg P \wedge \neg Q$
17.  $PQR$
18.  $P \wedge Q \wedge R \wedge S$
19.  $P \vee Q \vee R \vee S$
20.  $P \vee (Q \vee (R \vee S))$
21.  $p \wedge q \wedge r \wedge s$
22.  $P \wedge Q \vee R \wedge S$
23.  $P \rightarrow Q \rightarrow R \rightarrow S$
24.  $P \leftrightarrow Q \wedge R$
25.  $P \wedge Q \leftrightarrow R$
26.  $X \vee Y \vee Z$
27.  $\neg (P \wedge Q \wedge R \rightarrow S)$
28.  $\neg P \& \neg Q$
29.  $((P \vee Q))$
30.  $P \wedge Q \wedge R \rightarrow S \vee T \wedge R$
31.  $P \wedge Q \vee R \rightarrow S \vee T \wedge R$
32.  $P \rightarrow Q \vee R \vee S \vee T \vee R$
33.  $(P \rightarrow Q \vee R) \vee S \vee (T \wedge R)$


